HEADWORD: Mythologizer
<hw>My*thol"o*gi`zer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or
that which, mythologizes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Imagination has always been, and still is, in a narrower sense,
the great <qex>mythologizer</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mythologue</ent>⟦br⟧
